Below is a small Go web application using AWS SDK for Go v2. It serves a frontend, accepts a Step Functions ARN plus key/value inputs, converts the form into JSON, starts the Step Functions execution, and displays an activity log.

AWS SDK for Go v2 can load credentials and region from the normal AWS credential/config chain using config.LoadDefaultConfig. Step Functions executions are started through the StartExecution API, which accepts a state machine ARN and JSON input.

